Another radical candidate (short version)

If you want something even more disruptive:

programmable matter foam

A lightweight foam made of micro-lattice cells that can change stiffness, shape, or conductivity.

Applications:
	•	adaptive buildings
	•	impact-absorbing vehicles
	•	morphing aircraft
	•	medical implants
	•	soft robotics

⸻

The deeper rule for world-changing materials

The most impactful materials usually do one of these:
	1.	make something cheaper by orders of magnitude
	2.	enable mass replication
	3.	unlock a new physical capability

Paper did #1 and #2.

Semiconductors did #3.

A future material that does all three would reshape civilization again.

